USA: U.S. mine workers, coal operators in pact.U.S. mine workers, coal operators in pact.The United Mine Workers of America said on Tuesday that it struck a deal with the Bituminious Coal Operators Association that would improve wages, health insurance and pension benefits.The pact includes wage bonuses of $600 a year for 1997 and 1998 to union members employed by BCOA companies. It also calls for holding early negotiating sessions next year in advance of the current contract's expiration on August 31, 1998, the union said.